      "writtenOn": "2018-07-24T16:55:44Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "origin_upper_left only affects the frag coord: https://www.khronos.org/registry/OpenGL/extensions/ARB/ARB_fragment_coord_conventions.txt\n\n    The scope of this extension deals *only* with how the fragment\n    coordinate XY location appears during programming fragment processing.\n    Beyond the scope of this extension are coordinate conventions used\n    for rasterization or transformation.\n\nTo affect the front face, there\u0027s https://www.khronos.org/registry/OpenGL-Refpages/gl4/html/glClipControl.xhtml\n\nI\u0027ve added origin_upper_left to the GM so we can verify it behaves as we expect on all devices.",
      "parentUuid": "3c9c28bc_6bb855cc",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 695,
        "startChar": 24,
